race.comment: KINGTONDO (9) is another winning chance for the smart Freedman yard. he raced forward and looked a run short on debut and then led over this distance at Geelong beaten a long neck. Fitter again and will take beating. FROGS (14) has switched to the premier stable and expect him to be ready for the first-up assignment. Went well enough in town on debut and has jumped out twice. Draws a low barrier and John Allen sticks with the gelding. The betting will be key. EPOCH (3) resumes and finished his previous campaign with an impressive effort at Ballarat over a mile. Kicks off over a longer sprint this time and the in-form Yendall continues his association. Has plenty of scope for improvement. LEFT ON READ (5) runs along and went close at Wangaratta third-up. He also has claims. Ditto PARISH PRIEST (10) who is also fourth up for Maher and he has the blinkers on for the first time.
